<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Crew 2, Wizards 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Ansil Elcock scored in the 70th minute  
Sunday to give the Columbus Crew a 2-1 MLS victory over the Kansas 
City Wizards. 
</P>
<P>
	Elcock's third goal of the season, assisted on by Brian  
Maisonneuve and Brian McBride, improved the Crew's record to 14-7 
and gave them 32 points, moving second-place Columbus within two 
points of first-place D.C. United in the Eastern Conference. 
</P>
<P>
	McBride took the ball from two Kansas City defenders and passed  
it to Maisonneuve around midfield. He sent it to Elcock, who shot 
from 15 yards out and beat Kansas City goalkeeper David Winner. 
</P>
<P>
	The Crew's Robert Warzycha opened the scoring with his first  
goal of the season in the 22nd minute. The ball caromed off Kansas 
City defender Alexi Lalas, hit the goal post and went in. Brian 
West and Maisonneuve got assists. 
</P>
<P>
	Chris Brown of Kansas City (6-16) made the score 1-1 in the 55th  
minute on a low shot from 25 yards out that also hit the post and 
eluded Crew goalkeeper Mark Dougherty. The goal was Brown's fourth. 
</P>
<P>
	The Crew had a 15-12 edge in shots. Winner made five saves and  
Dougherty had three. 
</P>
<P>
	Kansas City played the last 11 minutes with 10 players after  
defender Uche Okafor was ejected for tackling from behind. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
