<HEADLINE> D.C. United Tops Mutiny in Shootout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Tom Presthus made two saves in the shootout,  
including one in the final round, and Jaime Moreno scored the 
deciding goal to give D.C. United a shootout 3-2 victory over the 
Tampa Bay Mutiny Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	D.C. United outscored the Mutiny 3-2 in the shootout after the  
teams deadlocked 2-2 in regulation. 
</P>
<P>
	Steve Ralston and Josh Keller both scored for Tampa Bay, while  
A.J. Wood and Roy Lassiter scored for D.C. United. The shootout was 
tied at 2 after three rounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Presthus then stopped Raul Diaz Arce's shot, and Moreno put a  
soft shot past goalie Scott Garlick that rolled slowly into the 
goal. Jorge Salcedo tried to tie it for Tampa Bay, but Presthus 
smothered his shot to seal the victory. 
</P>
<P>
	Musa Shannon had a goal and an assist for Tampa Bay as the  
Mutiny took a 2-1 lead in the second half. He scored his team-high 
11th of the season in the 40th minute to tie the score 1-1 and set 
up Steve Trittschuh's second goal of the season early in the second 
half. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 52nd minute, Dominic Kinnear sent a pass to Shannon, who  
redirected it into the middle, and Trittschuh put the ball into the 
net while standing in-between four D.C. United defenders. 
</P>
<P>
	Trittschuh later was given a red card in the 73rd minute for  
dangerous play after tackling Moreno from behind. 
</P>
<P>
	D.C. United tied it in the 85th minute when Wood headed in Marco  
Etcheverry's corner kick from in front. It was Wood's career-high 
sixth goal. 
</P>
<P>
	Etcheverry, playing his first game with D.C. United since June  
after playing with the Bolivian national team and then being 
injured, scored the game's first goal, heading a Lassiter pass in 
during the 17th minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Tampa Bay tied it in the 40th minute when Carlos Valderrama sent  
a ball into the box that Shannon dove and headed in. 
  	   	
