<HEADLINE> Strawberry Has 3 RBIs in Minors Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Darryl Strawberry continued his comeback  
from a drug suspension Saturday with two hits and three RBIs in a 
Triple-A doubleheader. 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry went 2-for-3 in the opener and 0-for-1 in the  
nightcap, sitting out most of the game after a 30-minute rain delay 
in the second inning. 
</P>
<P>
	In the opener, Strawberry doubled in the second inning and  
singled in the fifth to drive in two runs in the Columbus Clippers' 
7-4 victory over Charlotte in the International League. 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry, who batted fourth and played left field in the first  
game, also struck out looking in the third. He is batting .375 
(6-for-16) in five games with Columbus. 
</P>
<P>
	His only at-bat in the second game was a groundout that drove in  
a run. Charlotte beat Columbus 4-1. 
  	   	
