<DOCNO> APW19990808.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-08 23:21:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  A Lady From Dixie Wins at Del Mar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- A Lady From Dixie took command in  
midstretch and then held off the late challenge of Manistique to 
win Sunday's $300,000 Chula Vista Handicap by a half-length at Del 
Mar. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Chris Antley, A Lady From Dixie covered 1 1-16 miles  
in 1:43 2-5 and paid $17.20, $3.60 and $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Manistique returned $2.20 and $2.10 as the wagering favorite.  
Yolo Lady was another half-length back in third and paid $2.10 to 
show. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory, worth $180,000, was A Lady From Dixie's fifth in  
nine career starts. The 4-year-old trained by D. Wayne Lukas 
carried high weight of 124 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Manistique, ridden by Chris McCarron, has won eight of 10 career  
starts. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990808.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-08 23:21:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  A Lady From Dixie Wins at Del Mar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- A Lady From Dixie took command in  
midstretch and then held off the late challenge of Manistique to 
win Sunday's $300,000 Chula Vista Handicap by a half-length at Del 
Mar. 
</P>
