<DOCNO> APW19990808.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-08 11:50:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Grant Pokes Fun at Running Style </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Run Hugh, run!  
</P>
<P>
	For one scene in his latest movie ``Mickey Blue-Eyes,'' Hugh  
Grant draws from a past filming experience to help inspire his 
athletic abilities. 
</P>
<P>
	``There was a scene in (Four Weddings and A Funeral) where I  
chased Andie MacDowell and I was very humiliated when the director 
came up to me and said 'Hugh, could you please run like a man?' 
Which I thought I was,'' Grant says in the September issue of 
Cosmopolitan magazine. 
</P>
<P>
	``Since then, everyone's always begged me not to run in films,  
so I thought 'Let's write a whole scene about it.' Let the whole 
world laugh with me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The result? A segment where Grant speeds down the street so  
awkwardly with co-star Jeanne Tripplehorn that it looks like his 
legs are tied together. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990808.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-08 12:12:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Bodies Found in Philippines Collapse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CEBU, Philippines (AP) -- Rescuers recovered three more bodies on  
Sunday from the rubble of a building that collapsed while under 
construction in the central Philippines, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	Five bodies have been found so far, including that of a worker  
who had made tapping sounds a day earlier, police investigators 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	At least eight workers are believed still trapped in the ruins  
of the four-story building, which collapsed before dawn Saturday in 
Cebu City apparently due to a damaged main concrete column. Eleven 
other workers were injured. 
</P>
<P>
	Richard Sison, one of those leading the search and rescue  
efforts, said rescuers heard somebody tapping an object against a 
thick concrete slab Saturday morning, prompting rescuers to hasten 
efforts to bore a hole through it. 
</P>
<P>
	Rescuers managed to find the worker Sunday but he was already  
dead, Sison said. 
</P>
<P>
	He said hope was fading that other workers could still be found  
alive. 
</P>
<P>
	Cebu, 360 miles south of Manila, is the country's second-largest  
urban center. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
